{"questionId":"2804431","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function can be written in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2804431","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the values of h and k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}